ent-RMCCoatWeYaPilot-name = Weston-Yamada Pilot formal-jacket
ent-RMCCoatWeYaPilot-desc = A suit-style jacket with a fur lined collar and golden epaulettes signifying rank. Worn by Weston-Yamada qualified civilian Pilots, akin to old Earth formal Pilots-wear.

ent-RMCCoatPaP-name = PaP uniform jacket
ent-RMCCoatPaP-desc = A People's Armed Police service jacket featuring small dispersed para-aramid inserts providing the barest of defensive functionality, and a Personal Light Unit rig.

ent-RMCCoatTSEPAHighVisVest-name = TSEPA hazard vest
ent-RMCCoatTSEPAHighVisVest-desc = A green and white striped (high-visibility) polyester vest commonly used by TSEPA personnel.

ent-RMCCoatTSEPAHighVis-name = TSEPA high-vis jacket
ent-RMCCoatTSEPAHighVis-desc = A green and white striped (high-visibility) polyester vest commonly used by TSEPA personnel.

ent-RMCCoatTSEPAFormal-name = TSEPA police formal jacket
ent-RMCCoatTSEPAFormal-desc = A heavy woolen formal coat commonly used by TSEPA Constables. Empire and Honor, Bound by Duty. Duty Beyond Borders, Justice Across Worlds.

ent-RMCCoatTSEPA-name = TSEPA police jacket
ent-RMCCoatTSEPA-desc = A black polyester jacket with a silver Sakura emblem of the TSEPA pinned to it. Empire and Honor, Bound by Duty. Duty Beyond Borders, Justice Across Worlds.

ent-RMCCoatJacketGeneral-name = general's jacket
ent-RMCCoatJacketGeneral-desc = A black trench coat with gold metallic trim. Flashy, highly protective, and over-the-top. Fit for a king - or, in this case, a General. Has quite a few pockets.

ent-RMCCoatExpensiveFur-name = expensive fur-lined trench-coat
ent-RMCCoatExpensiveFur-desc = A luxurious fur-lined, antique-styled trench coat that exudes classic noir elegance. This exquisite garment is far beyond the average person's budget, accessible only to high-level executives and elite military personnel.

ent-RMCCoatBureauMarshal-name = CMB marshal jacket
ent-RMCCoatBureauMarshal-desc = A thick and stylish black leather jacket with a Marshal's badge pinned to it. The back is enscribed with the powerful letters of 'MARSHAL' representing justice, authority, and protection in the outer rim.

ent-RMCCoatBureauDeputy-name = CMB deputy jacket
ent-RMCCoatBureauDeputy-desc = A thick and stylish black leather jacket with a Marshal's Deputy badge pinned to it. The back is enscribed with the powerful letters of 'DEPUTY' representing justice, authority, and protection in the outer rim.

ent-RMCCoatBureauTrenchCoatBeige-name = beige trench-coat
ent-RMCCoatBureauTrenchCoatBeige-desc = A worn, tan, old style trench-coat. A classic of noir-style apparel.

ent-RMCCoatBureauTrenchCoatGrey-name = grey trench-coat
ent-RMCCoatBureauTrenchCoatGrey-desc = A worn, grey, old style trench-coat. When a bum sees a cop coming, he don't stick around.

ent-RMCCoatBureauTrenchCoatBrown-name = brown trench-coat
ent-RMCCoatBureauTrenchCoatBrown-desc = A worn, brown, old style trench-coat. When a bum sees a cop coming, he don't stick around.

ent-RMCCoatExpensiveFurAlt-name = expensive fur-lined trench-coat
ent-RMCCoatExpensiveFurAlt-desc = A luxurious fur-lined, antique-styled trench coat that exudes classic noir elegance. This exquisite garment is far beyond the average person's budget, accessible only to high-level executives and elite military personnel.

